 Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Robert Nowers was born about 1248, in Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1248–":"umbes 1248–Surnud","1279–Male":"1279–Surnud","1248–Male":"1248–Surnud","1248":"1248","1279":"1279","about 1248":"umbes 1248","Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Knossington, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1248–":"noin 1248–Kuollut","1279–Male":"1279–Kuollut","1248–Male":"1248–Kuollut","1248":"1248","1279":"1279","about 1248":"noin 1248","Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Knossington, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1248–":"environ 1248–Décédé","1279–Male":"1279–Décédé","1248–Male":"1248–Décédé","1248":"1248","1279":"1279","about 1248":"environ 1248","Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Knossington, Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir Robert Nowers est né environ 1248, à Knossington, Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1248–":"um 1248–Verstorben","1279–Male":"1279–Verstorben","1248–Male":"1248–Verstorben","1248":"1248","1279":"1279","about 1248":"um 1248","Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Sir Robert Nowers wurde um 1248 in Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"about 1248